														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2242369">
									

<p>What <em>would</em> be a healthy practice? It was my understanding that most writers would feel frustrated if the only feedback they received from someone was &quot;meh&quot;/&quot;it's boring&quot;. Getting critique that gives the author a direction to follow shouldn't be like pulling teeth.</p>
<p>Of course, I'm personally more lenient on feedback once something's on the mainsite, but if we're going to encourage more people helping out writers with drafts, I'd want reviewers to be more concise so the author doesn't have to run around the issue of what people think needs to be fixed.</p>

							</div>

								
					
