				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/bland" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(663362); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=663362&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610180863" alt="Bland" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=663362)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/bland" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(663362); return false;" >Bland</a></span> <span class="odate time_1425360639 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Mar 2015 05:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2243313">
									

<p>Do you think the right response should be &quot;I don't like your work - rewrite it THIS way&quot;? Honestly, that's the only expansion there is to some of them.</p>
<p>Sometimes there isn't much really TO say beyond &quot;This is boring.&quot; It's not the critic's job to give the author the way to tell the author how fix everything.</p>
<p>There are a LOT of short critiques (&quot;This is confusing&quot; &quot;This is self contradictory&quot; &quot;This isn't interesting&quot; etc.) that really don't require justification or an essay on each point.</p>
<p>&quot;Meh&quot; is simply shorthand for &quot;Your cheese sandwich needs more something.&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
					
